<topic id='business_definition_health_care_provider.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Health Care Provider - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Provider</xref>
 is an 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Provider</xref>
 is an 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
 acting as a direct provider of health care 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service">SERVICES</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Provider</xref>
 is a legal entity, or a sub-set of a legal entity, which may provide health care under 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_nhs_service_agreement">NHS SERVICE AGREEMENTS</xref>
; it may operate on one or more sites within and outside hospitals.  </p>
  <p>
This definition covers 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_local_authority">Local Authorities</xref>
 with social care responsibilities working in cooperation with an NHS 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Provider</xref>
 on nationally targeted and prioritised care as delivered within 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_care_spell">Care Spells</xref>
. Lead responsibility for such care may be solely led by one 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Provider</xref>
 or jointly shared by two or more 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Providers</xref>
 each of which must share equal responsibility.  </p>
  <p>
The following 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATIONS</xref>
 may act as 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Providers</xref>
:  </p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_gp_practice">GP Practice</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_nhs_trust">NHS Trust</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_nhs_foundation_trust">NHS Foundation Trust</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
Registered non-NHS Provider (e.g. 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_independent_provider">Independent Provider</xref>
, 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_independent_sector_healthcare_provider">Independent Sector Healthcare Provider</xref>
 etc)        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>Unregistered non-NHS Provider</p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_care_trust">Care Trust</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_local_authority">Local Authorities</xref>
            <p>with social care responsibilities</p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>Other agencies</p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>

</body>
